sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser (SPA)
    participant Django as Django Backend
    participant Cognito as AWS Cognito
    participant IdP as IdP (Entra ID)
    participant PostAuth as PostAuthFederationLink Lambda
    participant PreToken as PreTokenGeneration Lambda

    Note over Browser,PreToken: Post-Migration — Cognito user already exists<br/>with custom:django_id="42" set from previous SAML login.

    Note over Browser: Generate PKCE pair + state<br/>Store in sessionStorage

    Browser->>Django: GET /api/auth/discovery<br/>?email=user@example.com&state=nonce<br/>&code_challenge=Z&code_challenge_method=S256<br/>&redirect_uri=callback_url&client_id=X
    Note over Django: Look up IdP provider by email domain<br/>Build Cognito authorize URL
    Django-->>Browser: 302 Location: /oauth2/authorize?identity_provider=EntraSaml&...

    Browser->>Cognito: GET /oauth2/authorize?identity_provider=EntraSaml&...
    Cognito-->>Browser: 302 Location: IdP login page

    Browser->>IdP: GET (redirect)
    Note over IdP: User authenticates
    IdP->>Cognito: POST /oauth2/idpresponse (SAMLResponse)
    Note over Cognito: Validate assertion<br/>Match existing Cognito user by email<br/>(no new account created)<br/>Generate authorization code
    Cognito-->>Browser: 302 Location: callback_url?code=AUTH_CODE&state=nonce

    Note over Browser: Assert state == sessionStorage.federated_auth_nonce

    Browser->>Cognito: POST /oauth2/token<br/>grant_type=authorization_code&code=AUTH_CODE<br/>&code_verifier=VERIFIER&...
    Note over Cognito: Verify PKCE + trigger PostAuthentication
    Cognito->>PostAuth: PostAuthentication event<br/>userAttributes={email, sub, custom:django_id="42", identities:[SAML]}

    Note over PostAuth: _is_federated_login() = true<br/>Idempotent upsert — mapping already exists
    PostAuth->>Django: GET /api/internal/user-lookup/?email=user@example.com
    Django-->>PostAuth: 200 {"id":42,"email":"user@example.com"}
    PostAuth->>Django: POST /api/internal/link-cognito/<br/>{"django_user_id":42,"cognito_user_id":"sub-uuid","email":"user@example.com"}
    Django-->>PostAuth: 200 {"linked":true}
    PostAuth->>Cognito: AdminUpdateUserAttributes custom:django_id="42" (no-op)

    Cognito->>PreToken: PreTokenGeneration event<br/>userAttributes={email, sub, custom:django_id="42", identities:[SAML]}
    Note over PreToken: _login_method() returns "saml" + "EntraSaml"
    PreToken->>Django: POST /api/internal/login-access-check/<br/>{"email":"user@...","login_method":"saml","provider_name":"EntraSaml"}
    Django-->>PreToken: 200 {"allowed":true,"django_id":"42"}
    Note over PreToken: django_id="42" received in access-check response.
    PreToken-->>Cognito: claimsToAddOrOverride={django_id:"42"}

    Cognito-->>Browser: 200 {id_token, access_token, refresh_token}
    Note over Browser: SAML login complete.
